Search a string for the character "e":

Copy
let str = "this is a test";
let patt = new RegExp("e");
let res = patt.test(str);
console.log(res);
Output:


Description
The test() method tests for a match in a string.

This method returns true if it finds a match, otherwise it returns false.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
test()	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
RegExpObject.test(string)
Parameter Values
Parameter
string
Description
Required. The string to be searched
Return Value
Type	Description
Boolean	Returns true if it finds a match, otherwise it returns false
More Examples
Do a global search, and test for "Hello" and "Demo2s.com" in a string:

Copy
let str = "Hello world!";

// look for "Hello"
let patt = /Hello/g;
let result = patt.test(str);

// look for "Demo2s.com"
patt2 = /Demo2s.com/g;
result2 = patt2.test(str);
console.log(result);
console.log(result2);
Output:
